abstract: Intel’s success in selling its chips for high-end server computers have helped it weather pressure from tablet computers and continuing economic uncertainty.
snippet: Intel’s success in selling its chips for high-end server computers have helped it weather pressure from tablet computers and continuing economic uncertainty.
lead_paragraph: Despite facing one challenge after another in the first quarter, Intel posted strong profits on higher sales across its product line. The results surprised many investors, as well as Intel executives, who had projected a far bleaker quarter after a product recall, consolidation after two acquisitions and the effects of the Japanese earthquake on production.

headline.main: Intel’s Quarterly Profits Are Lifted by Sales of Chips for High-End Servers
headline.print_headline: Intel’s Quarterly Profits Are Lifted by Sales of Chips for High-End Servers
